        <p>Kid phones a school hotline an hour before someone phones in a bomb threat.  Unfortunately, the school hadn&#8217;t adjusted for the new DST switch, so he got hauled into juvenile detention for twelve days.  &#8220;County juvenile detention officials wanted to keep Webb in custody, Andrews said. &#8220;They wanted him to have a mental health evaluation because he wouldn&#8217;t admit to making the call.&#8221; &#8221;  Frightening.</p>

