<h3 class="date"><a href="/2007/feb/05/">&#x27a0;</a> February 5, 2007</h3>


<div class="row">
    <div class="span12">


    
    <div class="well" id="antifraud-measures-ineffective" >

        

        <h4><a class="taggedlink linklink" href="http://www.nytimes.com/2007/02/05/technology/05secure.html?ex=1328331600&amp;en=295ec5d0994b0755&amp;ei=5090&amp;partner=rssuserland&amp;emc=rss">Study Finds Web Antifraud Measure Ineffective - New York Times</a></h4>

        
            
        

        <p>I&#8217;ve always suspected that these &#8220;Select your image and don&#8217;t enter your password if you don&#8217;t see it&#8221; systems were broken &#8212; Asking users to behave differently when something is *missing*, which they&#8217;re liable to forget even *existed*, is not security by any stretch.</p>

        <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span10">
                
